verbose_text: Interestingly, there was no proportional decrease in the mRNA levels of Nestin (XREF_FIG C), suggesting that a fraction of NPCs are dividing even under Notch signalling inhibition; nonetheless, note that Notch signalling inhibition reduced but did not affect the increasing rate of Nestin mRNA levels in E9.5 explants, suggesting that NPC differentiation but not proliferation is the target of the Notch signalling pathway.
